OL,3,C'You don't want to take up a bed' -
OL,4,Chow the NHS is caring for patients at
OL,5,Chome
OL,7,F"Patients are having to be looked
OL,8,Fafter in corridors because there
OL,9,Faren't enough beds, which is not good
OL,10,Ffor them and not good for the staff
OL,11,Flooking after them."
OL,13,FTo ease the pressure on services,
OL,14,FSomerset NHS Foundation Trust are now
OL,15,Fcaring for 60-70 patients monthly with
OL,16,Frespiratory illnesses at home.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
