OL,3,C'You don't want to take up a bed' -
OL,4,Chow the NHS is caring for patients at
OL,5,Chome
OL,7,FDr Raines says this project doesn't
OL,8,Fonly ease the strain on hospitals, but
OL,9,Falso benefits the patients: "Research
OL,10,Fhas shown that patients recover more
OL,11,Fquickly in comfort of their own home
OL,12,Fand they're less likely to become de-
OL,13,Fconditioned.
OL,15,F"That means that if they're in
OL,16,Fhospital they may be in a bed the
OL,17,Fwhole time, they're isolated from
OL,18,Ffriends and family and the thins that
OL,19,Fthey'd normally do -like making a cup
OL,20,Fof tea.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/12
