OL,3,C'You don't want to take up a bed' -
OL,4,Chow the NHS is caring for patients at
OL,5,Chome
OL,7,FA lack of spaces in those community
OL,8,Fsettings often leaves people in
OL,9,Fhospital for longer than they need to
OL,10,Fbe, and the government knows this is a
OL,11,Fproblem it must address. In order to
OL,12,Fhelp ease pressure on NHS hospitals,
OL,13,Fadult social care must improve.
OL,15,FThere has been no shortage of damning
OL,16,Fdescriptions from Labour on the status
OL,17,Fof our health service and adult social
OL,18,Fcare system, but the Health Secretary
OL,19,FWes Streeting has also faced criticism
OL,20,Ffor not moving quickly enough.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/12
